# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HassarPath | Scene: JaeidPath4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "When they arrived back at the house, Sarah helped put all the items in Jasmine's room."
    new "When they arrived back at the house, Sarah helped put all the items in Jasmine's room."

    old "Then Jasmine shut the door, saying only that she had work to do."
    new "Then Jasmine shut the door, saying only that she had work to do."

    old "Sarah in turn was left alone by herself."
    new "Sarah in turn was left alone by herself."

    old "The house was quiet again."
    new "The house was quiet again."

    old "Jasmine seemed to make little if any noise while working."
    new "Jasmine seemed to make little if any noise while working."

    old "Jaeid was still away at the palace on whatever business had called him there."
    new "Jaeid was still away at the palace on whatever business had called him there."

    old "Sarah, for her part, simply walked about the house, inspecting it."
    new "Sarah, for her part, simply walked about the house, inspecting it."

    old "It was nice enough, speaking perhaps to Jaeid's station in life."
    new "It was nice enough, speaking perhaps to Jaeid's station in life."

    old "In Rosanna, she doubted this home would have impressed anyone. But from what she had seen, in this city, it was better than most."
    new "In Rosanna, she doubted this home would have impressed anyone. But from what she had seen, in this city, it was better than most."

    old "The only truly impressive building was the massive palace that sat upon the white rock, looming over the rest of the city."
    new "The only truly impressive building was the massive palace that sat upon the white rock, looming over the rest of the city."

    old "Sarah made a circle about the room."
    new "Sarah made a circle about the room."

    old "She carefully traced every object that seemed to stand out."
    new "She carefully traced every object that seemed to stand out."

    old "A small cabinet was filled with trinkets from seemingly many different cultures."
    new "A small cabinet was filled with trinkets from seemingly many different cultures."

    old "Some she could identify as hailing from her own country of Rosanna."
    new "Some she could identify as hailing from her own country of Rosanna."

    old "Some others she had never seen in her life. Far-East, perhaps, though she could not be certain."
    new "Some others she had never seen in her life. Far-East, perhaps, though she could not be certain."

    old "She explored the house for a while, if only because it gave her something to do."
    new "She explored the house for a while, if only because it gave her something to do."

    old "Finally, having turned about the house several times, and realizing she was starting to go in circles, Sarah decided to put herself to work."
    new "Finally, having turned about the house several times, and realizing she was starting to go in circles, Sarah decided to put herself to work."

    old "She was no slave, but that didn't mean she had to sit about and do nothing either."
    new "She was no slave, but that didn't mean she had to sit about and do nothing either."

    old "Sarah set about cleaning the house."
    new "Sarah set about cleaning the house."

    old "At first she decided to clean up the dishes that had been left about for too long."
    new "At first she decided to clean up the dishes that had been left about for too long."

    old "But with each passing moment, she grew bolder and decided to expand her project."
    new "But with each passing moment, she grew bolder and decided to expand her project."

    old "Sweeping the floor, gathering up trash, putting everything into order."
    new "Sweeping the floor, gathering up trash, putting everything into order."

    old "The work itself seemed to her a welcome distraction."
    new "The work itself seemed to her a welcome distraction."

    old "Before long, she also set her minds on one of the spare rooms in the house."
    new "Before long, she also set her minds on one of the spare rooms in the house."

    old "When she had first arrived, they had briefly spoken about her having the room to herself."
    new "When she had first arrived, they had briefly spoken about her having the room to herself."

    old "If she was to use it, it would need to be cleaned out as well, and wasn't it only right if she did so herself?"
    new "If she was to use it, it would need to be cleaned out as well, and wasn't it only right if she did so herself?"

    old "Sarah poured all of herself into the work."
    new "Sarah poured all of herself into the work."

    old "Minutes to hours, the day seemed to rush by where before it only crept."
    new "Minutes to hours, the day seemed to rush by where before it only crept."

    old "It was only when the front door opened and Jaeid entered, that Sarah became aware of the passing of the time."
    new "It was only when the front door opened and Jaeid entered, that Sarah became aware of the passing of the time."

    old "Outside, the sun had set."
    new "Outside, the sun had set."

    old "Ooh, you're home already."
    new "Ooh, you're home already."

    old "Sorry that it became so late. My meeting with the Khan ran late."
    new "Sorry that it became so late. My meeting with the Khan ran late."

    old "But it seems you've made yourself busy."
    new "But it seems you've made yourself busy."

    old "You like it?"
    new "You like it?"

    old "I think I got carried away after a while..."
    new "I think I got carried away after a while..."

    old "Jaeid smiled."
    new "Jaeid smiled."

    old "Perhaps I am more shocked."
    new "Perhaps I am more shocked."

    old "Shocked?"
    new "Shocked?"

    old "Yes, I never knew the house could look like this."
    new "Yes, I never knew the house could look like this."

    old "Sarah smiled, eager for the compliment."
    new "Sarah smiled, eager for the compliment."

    old "I also cleaned out the spare room, if that is okay."
    new "I also cleaned out the spare room, if that is okay."

    old "I thought I could use it?"
    new "I thought I could use it?"

    old "Of course. I don't think me or Jasmine used it for much of anything."
    new "Of course. I don't think me or Jasmine used it for much of anything."

    old "Having cleaned the room, Sarah knew that was true. Most of it had been garbage."
    new "Having cleaned the room, Sarah knew that was true. Most of it had been garbage."

    old "Thankfully, there had also been a bed there. Old to be sure, but functional."
    new "Thankfully, there had also been a bed there. Old to be sure, but functional."

    old "Speaking of her, where is Jasmine?"
    new "Speaking of her, where is Jasmine?"

    old "Working. I helped her buy supplies earlier."
    new "Working. I helped her buy supplies earlier."

    old "You want me to go get her?"
    new "You want me to go get her?"

    old "Best not to disturb her. When she gets into her work, she doesn't take well to being interrupted."
    new "Best not to disturb her. When she gets into her work, she doesn't take well to being interrupted."

    old "Sarah realized she was still a stranger to this place. Even to this household."
    new "Sarah realized she was still a stranger to this place. Even to this household."

    old "Jaeid looked about the room."
    new "Jaeid looked about the room."

    old "Are you hungry?"
    new "Are you hungry?"

    old "It suddenly dawned on Sarah that she was."
    new "It suddenly dawned on Sarah that she was."

    old "I am actually...I haven't eaten all day."
    new "I am actually...I haven't eaten all day."

    old "Do you want me to cook? I'm not really good at it, but I can try..."
    new "Do you want me to cook? I'm not really good at it, but I can try..."

    old "No, it is fine. I'll get us something to eat."
    new "No, it is fine. I'll get us something to eat."

    old "The night markets are overflowing with food stalls."
    new "The night markets are overflowing with food stalls."

    old "Jaeid left and returned in what seemed to Sarah as no time at all."
    new "Jaeid left and returned in what seemed to Sarah as no time at all."

    old "I just bought a few different things. I wasn't really sure what you liked."
    new "I just bought a few different things. I wasn't really sure what you liked."

    old "In a place like this, it was more of a kindness than she could have dared to hope for."
    new "In a place like this, it was more of a kindness than she could have dared to hope for."

    old "That's fine, I'm not a difficult eater."
    new "That's fine, I'm not a difficult eater."

    old "She didn't recognize any of the foods, but the smell of them was promising."
    new "She didn't recognize any of the foods, but the smell of them was promising."

    old "Sarah grabbed something that appeared bread-like to her."
    new "Sarah grabbed something that appeared bread-like to her."

    old "Imitating what she had seen Jaeid do, she dipped into a red paste and ate it."
    new "Imitating what she had seen Jaeid do, she dipped into a red paste and ate it."

    old "The flavors, all new and foreign, swirled about her mouth."
    new "The flavors, all new and foreign, swirled about her mouth."

    old "As she swallowed the food, the trace of the taste ran down her throat."
    new "As she swallowed the food, the trace of the taste ran down her throat."

    old "Wow, I've never had anything like this before."
    new "Wow, I've never had anything like this before."

    old "I'm glad you like it."
    new "I'm glad you like it."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah felt the taste that lingerd in her mouth, turn and transform into something else."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah felt the taste that lingerd in her mouth, turn and transform into something else."

    old "Before she knew it, the heat on her palate grew deeper and deeper."
    new "Before she knew it, the heat on her palate grew deeper and deeper."

    old "It didn't take long before her mouth felt like it was on fire."
    new "It didn't take long before her mouth felt like it was on fire."

    old "Sarah looked at Jaeid with a panicked expression, but only saw him laughing."
    new "Sarah looked at Jaeid with a panicked expression, but only saw him laughing."

    old "I'm sorry, Sarah. Here, drink this."
    new "I'm sorry, Sarah. Here, drink this."

    old "He pushed a pitcher of water towards her and Sarah eagerly drank."
    new "He pushed a pitcher of water towards her and Sarah eagerly drank."

    old "The cooled water reduced the burning sensation, though some of it lingered."
    new "The cooled water reduced the burning sensation, though some of it lingered."

    old "What was that!"
    new "What was that!"

    old "The food here is different, both the dishes but also the ingredients themselves."
    new "The food here is different, both the dishes but also the ingredients themselves."

    old "Some of the spices that are popular...well, it can take a bit to get used to."
    new "Some of the spices that are popular...well, it can take a bit to get used to."

    old "Sarah breathed through her mouth, cooling herself."
    new "Sarah breathed through her mouth, cooling herself."

    old "She could feel the sweat build on her face."
    new "She could feel the sweat build on her face."

    old "Well...it did taste good. But I think I'll go a bit slower."
    new "Well...it did taste good. But I think I'll go a bit slower."

    old "Still hungry, Sarah grabbed piece after piece off the table, exploring all the different foodstuffs that Jaeid had brought."
    new "Still hungry, Sarah grabbed piece after piece off the table, exploring all the different foodstuffs that Jaeid had brought."

    old "She could see him smiling as she was eating."
    new "She could see him smiling as she was eating."

    old "Nothing."
    new "Nothing."

    old "I'm just happy to see you happy."
    new "I'm just happy to see you happy."

    old "Sarah realized that for the first time, she had genuinely forgotten where she was."
    new "Sarah realized that for the first time, she had genuinely forgotten where she was."

    old "Without realizing, she had allowed herself to feel a moment of normalcy. She instantly felt guilty for it."
    new "Without realizing, she had allowed herself to feel a moment of normalcy. She instantly felt guilty for it."

    old "You are being nice to me. You and Jasmine both. It is more than I deserve."
    new "You are being nice to me. You and Jasmine both. It is more than I deserve."

    old "His voice was soft and filled with a pained kindness."
    new "His voice was soft and filled with a pained kindness."

    old "It might sound strange to you, but I see some of myself in you."
    new "It might sound strange to you, but I see some of myself in you."

    old "I told you of my old life and how I survived when I first came here as a slave."
    new "I told you of my old life and how I survived when I first came here as a slave."

    old "I spoke of the good things, but the truth is that there was plenty of pain there as well."
    new "I spoke of the good things, but the truth is that there was plenty of pain there as well."

    old "In a way, I think I wanted to give you a better experience than I had myself when I first came here."
    new "In a way, I think I wanted to give you a better experience than I had myself when I first came here."

    old "As a slave."
    new "As a slave."

    old "I know that you think your life is over, but the truth is that you have many decades more to live."
    new "I know that you think your life is over, but the truth is that you have many decades more to live."

    old "And you can build a life in this place, same as I managed."
    new "And you can build a life in this place, same as I managed."

    old "So I should just bow down?"
    new "So I should just bow down?"

    old "Jaeid looked at her sternly."
    new "Jaeid looked at her sternly."

    old "You should recognize the truth of the world."
    new "You should recognize the truth of the world."

    old "And what is that?"
    new "And what is that?"

    old "You are a people conquered."
    new "You are a people conquered."

    old "You may dispute that as you like, but it won't change the reality of your situation."
    new "You may dispute that as you like, but it won't change the reality of your situation."

    old "When I was captured, there were hundreds of others who sat down and cried about their lives."
    new "When I was captured, there were hundreds of others who sat down and cried about their lives."

    old "They threw up their hands and prayed to the Gods."
    new "They threw up their hands and prayed to the Gods."

    old "Why, they cried out."
    new "Why, they cried out."

    old "Why me? What have I done? Save me from this fate."
    new "Why me? What have I done? Save me from this fate."

    old "Over and over."
    new "Over and over."

    old "He kept his gaze on her."
    new "He kept his gaze on her."

    old "What do you think became of them? Do you think the Gods reached down and pulled them out?"
    new "What do you think became of them? Do you think the Gods reached down and pulled them out?"

    old "They failed to see the world for what it was, and so instead they fell into despair."
    new "They failed to see the world for what it was, and so instead they fell into despair."

    old "Their bodies were plenty strong. They could have worked themselves up. But they allowed their minds to falter."
    new "Their bodies were plenty strong. They could have worked themselves up. But they allowed their minds to falter."

    old "I just don't want that to happen to you."
    new "I just don't want that to happen to you."

    old "I don't deny that what has happened to you, your people, is not a tragedy."
    new "I don't deny that what has happened to you, your people, is not a tragedy."

    old "But I want you to know that your life need not be over."
    new "But I want you to know that your life need not be over."

    old "Like Jasmine, like myself, you can find a place in this society."
    new "Like Jasmine, like myself, you can find a place in this society."

    old "Live among the very people that destroyed my nation?"
    new "Live among the very people that destroyed my nation?"

    old "Your nation was destroyed. But you survived. Who will you make glad when you destroy yourself too?"
    new "Your nation was destroyed. But you survived. Who will you make glad when you destroy yourself too?"

    old "Sarah went quiet for a while."
    new "Sarah went quiet for a while."

    old "She contemplated his words."
    new "She contemplated his words."

    old "So much she had thought about surviving and escaping..."
    new "So much she had thought about surviving and escaping..."

    old "It had never even dawned on her that she might stay here and make a life for herself."
    new "It had never even dawned on her that she might stay here and make a life for herself."

    old "And what of the others?"
    new "And what of the others?"

    old "The people from my country."
    new "The people from my country."

    old "The truth is, some will suffer, some will prosper."
    new "The truth is, some will suffer, some will prosper."

    old "If your plan is to set all of the world right, perhaps best you start that journey with yourself."
    new "If your plan is to set all of the world right, perhaps best you start that journey with yourself."

    old "Sarah looked at Jaeid."
    new "Sarah looked at Jaeid."

    old "When she looked at him, spoke with him, it was easy to see him as a decent man."
    new "When she looked at him, spoke with him, it was easy to see him as a decent man."

    old "But it was also easy for her to forget that at the end, he was loyal to this place. These people."
    new "But it was also easy for her to forget that at the end, he was loyal to this place. These people."

    old "And the more she spoke with him, the more she realized, it was by threat."
    new "And the more she spoke with him, the more she realized, it was by threat."

    old "Jaeid seemed to genuinely believe in this society, the virtues that it preached."
    new "Jaeid seemed to genuinely believe in this society, the virtues that it preached."

    old "And how could he not, Sarah thought. His life had been transformed from a lowly servant to a man who had the Khan's ear."
    new "And how could he not, Sarah thought. His life had been transformed from a lowly servant to a man who had the Khan's ear."

    old "But he could she not hate them, Sarah thought. She who had been made from a princess to a slave."
    new "But he could she not hate them, Sarah thought. She who had been made from a princess to a slave."

    old "You have given me a lot to think about."
    new "You have given me a lot to think about."

    old "I am sorry if I sound harsh. I didn't mean to be."
    new "I am sorry if I sound harsh. I didn't mean to be."

    old "It is fine."
    new "It is fine."

    old "Better you speak honestly than tell me soft lies."
    new "Better you speak honestly than tell me soft lies."

    old "Sarah continued to eat."
    new "Sarah continued to eat."

    old "Eating, making conversation with Jaeid, there was an odd normalcy here."
    new "Eating, making conversation with Jaeid, there was an odd normalcy here."

    old "Despite all the dangers and the strangeness of this place, Sarah was able to feel at ease, if only for the night."
    new "Despite all the dangers and the strangeness of this place, Sarah was able to feel at ease, if only for the night."

